attachments.text:
Steven T. Seagle (born March 31, 1965) is an American writer who works in the comic book, television, film, live theater, video game, and animation, industries.
He is best known for his nationally acclaimed graphic novel memoir It's a Bird (Vertigo, May 2004), and as part of his Man of Action Studios (with Duncan Rouleau, Joe Casey and Joe Kelly) which created the animated Cartoon Network series Ben 10 responsible for both Cartoon Network's highest-rated single program and highest rated series premiere.
Seagle is also a founding member of Speak Theater Arts, creators of innovative live stage productions and is a former college instructor having taught at Ball State University, Pasadena City College and Mt. San Antonio College, where he also served as a coach for the Forensics team during many of their national championship seasons.

As a bit of a distraction, can we discuss the Immortal Sun card? 

A whole bunch of folks are saying “this will go in every edh deck,” though of course even they will admit that’s an exaggeration. The point remains that this is an edh card that many people are excited to put into several of their decks. 

Meanwhile, I cannot think of a single deck I want to put this into. My buddy has a Tana/Ravos build that looks like a good spot, but I seriously don’t think I’ll ever run this. The effects all feel minor to me, and pull in slightly different directions. Am I just crazy and super misevaluating this thing?
